
[1]sinfulness

   SIN'FULNESS, n.

   1. The quality of being sinful or contrary to the divine will;
   wickedness; iniquity; criminality; as the sinfulness of an action; the
   sinfulness of thoughts or purposes.

   2. Wickedness; corruption; depravity; as the sinfulness of men or of
   the human race.
